points

public ArrayList<Point> points
The points in this region

hide

public transient boolean hide
If this is true, then calls to draw() won't do anything, except for outlining if outline is true. This can be used to hide a region during editing, so that other regions can be seen better.

outline

public transient boolean outline
If this is true, a dark-green outline of this region's boundaries, with bezier curves resolved, will be drawn over the region. This can be used when editing a region to see exactly what area it takes up.

cubicBezier

public ArrayList<Integer> cubicBezier
The starting indexes of any sets of 3 points that should define a bezier curve. For example, if there are 6 points, and this array contains one element, namely the number 1, then the second, third, and fourth points will define a bezier curve, while the rest of the points will just define straight lines.

getBounds

private Polygon getBounds()
Creates a polygon that represents the bounds of this region. Bezier curves within this region are replaced by a set of points that define them before returning from this method.

Returns:
The points that define this region, with bezier curves resolved
